//key value pair
//no order of insertion 
//to iterate use .keyset method and store keys in a set of same type
not thread safe
only one null key
0(n) -> for putting, and getting
 0(n) -> map.containsKey 

 Interal-structure of hash map Key-value-bucket- hash function
  
inside there is array, the key is taken and sent to hash function
and returns fixed size string of bytes, a numerical value, the output is known as
hash code, hash value, or simply hash

same input will produce same output

----How data is stored-----
1) hashing the key 
2) index is found int index= hashCode&arraySize;
3) key and value is stored in the array index
----How data is retrived-----
1) hashing the key 
2) index is found int index= hashCode&arraySize;
3) once the correct bucket is found it checks for the key in that bucket, if its finds, it returns
4) .equals method is used to check the key, if key is string

 inputs ---> hash function---> one output called as collition this is stored in linked list (size 8) / after java 8 balanced binary search tress aka RB tree 
when linkedList size becomes 8 it will converted to RB tree

 rehashing 
 default size is 16 and load factor is 0.75 
 16*0.75= 12 when the size becomes 12 the size will double
 then rehasing happens, recalculated


 //Custom class
 every class extends object 
 so whenever Student student = new Student();
 this memory address is hashed whenever obj is created

HashMap
 time Complexity
 put, get,remove,contains key best o(1) worst o(logn)
 contains value best o(n) worst o(n)
 size best and worst o(1)
 
 --------------------LinkedHashMap-----------------

 insertion order will be maintained if accessorder is false . if true it works in the form of LRU where least used is sent to the top works by doubly linked list

 --------------------Garbage Collection-----------------
 object reference is not present for the object in the heap memory
 JVM will see if the object has any reference if its not present JVM will destroy automatically
 
 Phone phone = new Phone()---> Strong reference we are creating
System.gc();
-----------WeakReference
WeakReference<Phone> phoneweakref = new WeakReference(new Phone("Apple","10 pro"));
WeakReference for anything will be removed except for String as string is stored in string pool and will precistant throughout the lifecycle of the application